caption: Friendly, good caribbean food

Well this place was definitely worth the wait. Before I can even mention the food, I would like to say that the customer service is excellent!!! Eliz was very kind and patient while I was deciding on what to order.  To the food: All I can say if you definitely have to try this place. The goat Roti was pretty good. And the pumpkin veggies are out of this world! I will be returning here again. Thank you very much!!
Fantastic and delicious food, I liked the character this spot has, and the employees were very friendly. I will definitely come back again.
Cool

Top of the line out of this world delicious. It was worth the wait. And they have DOUBLES!!! I had roti and my sister had buss up shot... the meat was tender and fresh. We'll be back again and again. We'll take all of our out of state guests here too. 5 stars in my book from a 🇹🇹 gal!

This restaurant is my favorite. I visit plenty of restaurants but to this one I go the most. The crew is very helpful and the food they place on your table is so appetizing. I am always happy to have a nice dinner in this restaurant. I highly recommend this place.
Had a great experience here with my daughter. The food arrives fast and the customer service is just fantastic. Prices are convenient.
Fire doubles !!!!! And curry 🔥🔥

We went to Flambo for the first time last week on a recommendation from an acquaintance. He didn't recommend anything specific, so we based our choices on the descriptions on the website. We got fried wontons, pepper shrimp over rice, house special chow mein, cinnamon plantains, rice and beans, callaloo, phoulourie, plus a side of buss up shot and roti to use for the callaloo. Everything was amazing. The callaloo has a very earthy taste to it and was even better as leftovers, maybe because by the time we got home from picking up the food, everything had cooled a bit (we live about 30 minutes away). We will definitely go back.
I tried this spot already with my friend and I am addicted ever since. I like the great ambience and yummy dishes and beverages. Fantastic work.

True Trini food. I love the atmosphere, when you walk in, beside being greeted by a friendly hostess, you have a touch of Trinidad mardi gras lining the walls and the mannequin dressed for mardi gras. Calypso music playing softly in the background, although I felt like getting up and dance, but did so in my chair to the amusement of my friends. I ordered the corn soup first, which was very tasty and then my main course, buss up shot, with curry goat and curry chick peas.

I did not want to go into detail....as a fellow Trinidadian.  But since you decided to respond, let me give a detailed explanation why I gave a one star rating.  Firstly, it is not 3am, it is currently 5:28pm EST. My rating was posted 3pm 12/14/2020.  Secondly, because of the raving reviews, I drove from Marlton NJ all the way to Philly despite today’s weather and the traffic, to patronize a local TRINI restaurant. I ordered 2 orders of goat roti (buss up), 2 orders of goat roti dhalpurie, 1 order of shrimp wontons and 1 order of chicken chowmein.  I was very much unsatisfied with the taste of EVERYTHING ordered. The goat was very oily, the channa was watery and tasteless, the wontons were soggy, the chicken chowmein was too soft and drowned in some kind of brown sauce. It did not taste like authentic Trini chowmein at all...(was thrown in the garbage) The buss up shot was actually ok,  but the portion was too small for the price.  I did not bother to taste the dhalpurie, but I take  my dad’s word for it.....he wasn’t impressed....and he is an honest critique.  As a born Trini who grew up in Brooklyn, and moved to the suburbs, I was more than willing to drive over an hour for real Trini food, and support a local Trini,  especially during this Covid pandemic.... but to say the least, I was extremely disappointed.  One more thing I must say though, the person who called to let me know the order was ready, and who met me at the door, was very pleasant, quite professional and created a great first impression. It is quite unfortunate that the food did not meet my expectation. Hence the reason for my one star review.
Soo good lol

Always the go to spot when I am craving some really good Caribbean food. Seriously yum!  We had the Beef Patties, Stew Chicken + Roti, & Curry Shrimp Buss-up-shot. I know it was good because my boyfriend (from Tobago) did a happy dance while eating it. Hahah I need those recipes! lol in all seriousness though, thanks for the speedy delivery and great food! =)

False advertisement because as you can see my house (nothing special) chow mein looks absolutely nothing like the picture. Where the snap peas, string beans and the peas that you see in the original pic thats on the website. The oxtails horrible, rice trash and I know that's not suppose to be cabbage.  I absolutely love food, but I will not be returning back.
Ordered from door dash or Grubhub The roti was flavorless and the buss up shut was too. The channa was horrible I couldnt eat the meal. I threw it all in the trash. What a waste!

I meet friends in this place  a lot! This is my favorite restaurant to have a bite.  I go there many times. The meals are excellent, the staff is friendly and the cost is decent. I enjoy going in this spot to have a tasty dinner.
I really enjoyed their dishes. I always get good service here. The place is neat and the cashiers are always nice. Would recommend to others.
I regularly come by purchasing some food in this place. I like the prompt service and well prepared dishes. They never disappoint.
Extraordinary atmosphere and very personal service. The meals were fresh and yummy. Will surely recommend this restaurant to friends and family. Fair rates and large meals. Keep up the great work.
Nice ambiance and great food

I’m definitely shocked at the reviews. Being a Trini and from New York I have experienced multiple Caribbean restaurants but this fell short for me! I ordered a veggie buss up and an oxtail platter. The curry was very watery, lacked seasoning/salt and the serving amount could have been more. There were barely any potatoes. The oxtail was ok but the rice and peas were served with Basmati rice so it didn’t taste too authentic to me. The people were nice but don’t tell me you did me a favor by giving me extra oxtail when there were only four in there. If that was extra, what was I getting before? Two pieces?! At least I was greeted with a smile 🤷🏽‍♀️

Please don’t waste your money buying food from this place. I got the oxtails which was not seasoned well, I also had what we call Pelau in Trinidad,  it’s basically well seasoned  rice with pigeon peas,  this was not Palau, it was  made with basmati rice and they poured brown sauce over it and threw some beans in there, and the veggies were mediocre,  definitely not a Trinidadian traditional style Pelau. I was very disappointed.
Fresh seafood served daily. Steady clientele.

I go to this lovely spot quite often! This is my favorite spot to pass a nice evening.  I visit this place at least once a month. The meals are excellent, the team is professional and the charge is affordable. I enjoy going in this spot over a decent supper.
My favorite location for caribbean food. Food with real quality ingredients.  Next time I'll be back with my relatives. This place has great reviews for a reason.
Great quality, really enjoyed the oxtails and red snapper!!!
Very good food and very friendly service.
This is the best buss up shot roti ive had since being in NYC.. it was so good with the curry chicken.. Thank you
Would definitely recommend visiting this place. Awesome character, delightful food, great service. 5 stars.

Not my first time ordering wont be my last. I ordered the corn soup it was very tasty missing dumplings but still I ate it all with enjoyment.  The wontons were good sauce reminds of Trini. Buss was flaky and light. Curry was properly colored and flavorful. Curry mussels perfect jerk wings perfect!!! When Covid-19 is over I’m hosting something here!!!!!  #Nadiaapprovesflambo!

Ordered take out from here during the covid-19 epidemic. Staff was friendly ordered pepper shrimp chow mein which was okay. Platter had 6 jumbo shrimps which were very tasty a bunch of vegetables and hardly no chow mein which was a bit dissatisfying. Paid about $16 which wasn't too bad but platter was not fulling.

I expected more.  I read the reviews and have come to the conclusion that a lot of them dont know what true Carribean food should taste like.   Im greatly disappointed.  The chicken tasted old and very dry, the chick peas were undercooked and the rice and beans were very dry and bland.
Stew Chicken was not good, and they overcharged me for my meal. Why am I paying $18 for a small? Waste of money
The food and service were above our expectations. I surely loved the vibes of this restaurant. Extraordinary place to take my family out for lunch.

The service was good and the curry mussels were great. These were the best mussels hands down. After looking for a new Caribbean that will not disappoint my taste buds, Flambo definitely satisfied my expectations. The owner was very hospitable and friendly. The only thing is, I wanted more mussels because I could not get enough. Next time, I will certainly order more than one serving. I than finally found a new place to go for that authentic Caribbean taste.
I really like the dishes and customer service, fantastic area next to my home. The staff members are always helpful. Will visit here again.
Had a very good experience in here with my son. The food comes fast and the service is just great. Prices are affordable.
This was my first time here and the food was awesome!! Great customer , beautiful ambiance!! Will definitely be back 🇹🇹🇹🇹🇹🇹

This place is definitely one of the finest place to eat in the region. Anytime I come to this place I am exceedingly happy. They hold their high  standard service and the topmost level of food  they offer. You no doubt will love this restaurant. Warmly  recommended.
You have no idea what's awaiting. This fabulous restaurant is exactly what's needed for a group, family or friends Reservations accepted.

I ordered the curry goat, the mac and cheese, and the fried plantains.  All three were superb!   I was especially impressed by the Mac and cheese- it was jam packed with intricate flavors from the vegetables and spices used.  The waiter was hospitable, helping my party choose their dinners and accompanying drinks (which were soo unique and fresh).  Oh and BYOB...Amazing dinner at an amazing restaurant!
The food is so delicious and the service was great! My favorite is the curried mussels, almost wanted to ask the chef for the recipe! Always great when I come here. Kudos to the owners!

This is a diamond in the rough that you rarely find in Philadelphia. I am a big lover of noodles and I saw on the menu that they had chow mein. In my mind chow mein consisted ofdeep fried wonton noodles but at this restaurant the noodles are sautee and soft and chewable and very flavorful and the sauce is amazing I ordered the house chow mein.absolutely amazing my taste buds are jumping you should definitely come and check out this restaurant. For all of my Caribbean that look for that down home cooking come to Flambo this is where the flavor is at my people.

First and last time here. Really wanted this place to be great seeing how it's really hard to find decent Caribbean food in Philly and after reading the reviews it was kinda like a slap in the face. Idk if the cook was having a bad day or just being overall lazy. But everything that was ordered was either undercooked or overcooked. Smh. Should've known better when I walked in and saw what the server looked like. (they were cool) but definitely should've known better.

Best Trini Spot hands down in the city. I’ve gone twice and look forward to coming again to try more items from the menu. BYOB and the customer service is on point. Manager walked around BOTH times I was there and asked how was everything. The curry mussels were my favorite.
Service a bit slow but the food was delicious. Cool vibe.

I got curried chicken with buss up shut and curried muscles. My husband got the fish Escabeche. Everything was so amazing. Coming from a person who’s family is from Trinidad the food was so amazing. I loved my food and his. Definitely will be back!!!
Great service and the food was amazing. Went in the middle of the day for lunch and it was just my party.
I had an awesome time in this restaurant. We loved the amazing atmosphere and the food. The staff are super attentive. I am glad we ultimately decided to try this place.
The food is constantly fresh and delicious, staff members hands out good service. I like the cleanliness and ambience. Will come visit again.
Was going to a show at the Meet and almost walked past this place as the entrance is small.  Great food and nice staff.  BYOB

Good customer service but bland food and not what i thought it would be. Ok some give you five stars and others don't your right you can't please everyone but learn how to take criticism that's what you lack looking at the comments you read your reviews and figure out how to make it better but you can't even do that and that's probably why your  business has been slow for two years good thing i write about business like yours so people know what to expect. Have a great day

My son and I enjoyed a terrific combination of chicken and shrimp roti. The seasonings were amazing and the roti was so delicious. If anyone is going to be visiting the Met nearby, I can think of no better place to stop in for lunch or dinner beforehand than Flambo. (Great professional service, too!)
It was okay!
Food was good!
Great Service and very insightful when asking about the history of the restaurant. If you are looking for a nice ethnic restaurant to stop at before your Met show this is the place to go!
Good vegan/vegetarian options
Service was fine but I definitely got food poisoning from the chicken curry. My boyfriend got the curry goat and it was all bone and tendons. Food was bland overall.
Very nice place and a great service

I had a great dining experience in Flambo Restaurant. The food was delicious and the customer service was great  The only way you will regret coming here is if you have super boring food taste because nothing you get here has basic or bland flavoring. The meats are incredibly spiced and saucy, aka what ALL meat should be like. It's not overly fatty or salty, just right. The curry goat and oxtail are both-you know I'm just gonna stop, go order them and find out.
Delicious food and pleasant atmosphere. Best corn soup ever!! Will definitely be back to try more selections from the fabulous menu.
Apps were excellent...wonder how they can top dinner?!?  Has limited menu when there is a performance at The MET, but still a great selection.  Definitely a do over!!
I love Rambo's the Caribbean and Curry food is so good I love it excellent

Awesomeness!!!!!!!! This place has a wonderful decor! Great food! Plantains were perfectly glaced with a crispy coat and gooey inside..chicken wings were seasoned to perfection! Curry chicken!!! Don't get me started!! Love it!

Ate here on a whim before a show at the Met last night. It was horrible. They were nice  and accommodated us without a res, but the service was mediocre, we were given a barely cool carafe of water, no other beverages were offered ("can I get you something to drink?") The menu was very limited, the one online shows way more than we were handed. The food was bleh. 2 of us got the Pelau and I got the chicken stew which was NOT a stew and not a sign of tomatoes which is deacribed as the base on the menu I was handed. Pelau was bland and boring. Also our plates were piled high with rice but 3 little chunks of chicken, about half a breast. And half of my chicken was barely cooked thru. 3 meals, no drinks, $50???? Couldn't pay me to go back.
What a wonddrful experience.  Thank you
👌🏼The Ambiance is great the food is great!👍🏼
Can't rate this restaurant yet because days that they have events you can't order take out,  so I went to my Jamaican  spot because I can always buy to go and dine in if I want.
Wow!! Food was delicious,what a warm and welcoming experience, the atmosphere and ambiance gives the feeling of home. Defenitely will be back and highly recommend.
Cozy place to enjoy some quality food
Food is not worth the price, place looks good in pictures only, and service was below par
Gotta try this place
Nice byob.  Good Trinidadian food.  Some Chinese flavor.
Very welcoming place and the food was great! The owner came out and met all the patrons after they were served.
Food and service were absolutely exceptional

I always look forward to a visit to Flambo Caribbean.  The atmosphere is outstanding, the food is all wonderfully made and delicious, and the service is spectacular.   This is a very special location with a very interesting menu.  Looking forward to another visit....soon.  Thank you for the great service!  Ron

I have now visited several times. Each visit, the service has been incredible. Kevin is always very helpful with making recommendations, and Anthony does an incredible job creating authentic cuisine from Trinidad. The location is also very convenient as it is right by the Met, which is ideal for a pre-show dinner or, just a night out.

I am baffled by all these raving reviews. The food was disgusting. I had a nearly inedible goat curry that was 90% bone and fat drowning in a nasty-tasting curry sauce. The side of "fried" plantains was a soggy slop we could not bear to take more than one bite of. Would not recommend.

If you’re looking for authentic Caribbean food, this is the place! The atmosphere is great and the food is even better! Our group ate blackened shrimp, chicken chow mein, chicken stew, fried wontons, and lava cakes. Everything was delicious! The wait staff was nice and pleasant, as well! Highly recommend and definitely going back! Thank you Flambo for a great night out!
Authentic rotis - best I've had state side.
Amazing food! Amazing service!
The Food Here Was Great. The owner was very friendly.
Great food, prices and Music!!!
You are right there was a misunderstanding somewhere along the line. Thank you for the extra wings. And the roti and Dahl puri was amazing.
Super good food. BYOB. Felt at home and Kev is great with food recommendations

This place is amazing. They were THE busiest they have ever been and all of our food plus all of the service was excellent. I ordered the bus up shot, stew chicken, macaroni pie and vegetables. The roti was to die for, just like mom used to make.

You will not regret coming here! We came during one of the restaurant's busiest days ever, and despite this business being run solely by ONE man, we got amazing service. The food: Exceptional. You could taste the time and love put into it with each bite. The atmosphere, the food, and the heart and soul that this establishment was built with are as authentic as they come.
Excellent, unique food. Very nice staff. Would happily go back.

This was my first time at Flambo, and I was really excited to find a West Indian restaurant in the city! Unfortunately the restaurant was super crowded, and there was a shortage of waiters. After we had to wait 50 minutes for our appetizers, we asked to speak to the manager, who wasn’t available because he was one of only two cooks in the kitchen! Although this may be true, the waitress clearly forgot to put in our order given that other tables that arrived after us received their food before us. During this entire wait, the waitress never came back to take our orders for the main course and never updated on our food nor refilled our water. It’s unfortunate the service was so bad, because the food was pretty good!

Let me first say, the food was good. If they work on servicing a large crowd efficiently, they'll have it all together. This is a prime location since the Philadelphia MET is next door, it they have more people all around to give excellent service, business will stay steady.
Great food!!! Great experience!!!
Nice atmosphere call ahead for Roti

After reading mixed reviews about the restaurant I wanted to find out for myself. The decor was beautiful although the floor needs to be redone. I was greeted by the owner who presented the menu, and so, I ordered the veggie platter anticipating a flavorful dish....unfortunately it was a total let down. The patchoi consisted mainly of chopped tomatoes and onions and totally lacked flavor. It felt like they're trying to bulk up the veggies with tomatoes and onion which really is a cheap trick. The pumpkin was delicious but the rice was very bland. God alone knows how the meat dishes would have tasted if they couldn't get simple vegetables right. This kind of cooking is not truly representative of our rich Trinidadian cuisine. The cook/chef needs another introduction to authentic Caribbean seasonings as well as new taste buds. It's a shame that these people are passing off mediocre cooking as Caribbean cuisine. I do not recommend going there for true Caribbean cuisine.  Response to Owner  No explanation was needed because we came from the same place...you know that. Patchoi, bok-choi, etc. is generally cooked with roasted garlic and onions. Please don't confuse flavor with "heavy seasoning." Unfortunately there was overkill on the tomatoes and onions. It saddens me that a professional restaurant owner gets defensive rather than receptive about reviews. Psst! Every show has a season...I'm hopeful you'll incorporate authenticity when you film. All the best and have a nicer day.
Loved the food and the service, the chef came out to personally to greet us. I will be back with more friends next time and I look forward to their event in May.
Very average.  Best thing was the Yucca. Otherwise, the food tasted like they used Grace seasoning vs their own spice blends. I can cook with Grace at home.

Just left and was eating my food as I walked out the door. The food is amazing and the staff were fantastic. I highly recommend this place. The curry goat was everything 🥰🥰. The staff were very friendly. I love this place and came out of state just for their food.
Order the fish....fry or brown stew.........you will not be disappointed. It is fresh, WELL SEASONED......just delicious......great job Caribbean taste!!!!
Nice environment and tasty food... Love it

I was surprised to see all of the five star reviews for this restaurant. They all seem to be describing a different restaurant with dishes (like roti) that weren't on the menu when I visited. I ended up paying $14 for some overcooked noodles drowning in what tasted like ketchup and soy sauce, a handful of chopped vegetables and four sad, withered green beans arranged on top. I supplemented that with a side order of cold, crunchy plantains that weren't even ripe. One of the worst meals I have had in recent memories and the dining room wasn't even half full.

One of the nicest place to dine at in Philly! Anthony and his son Kevin are truly genuine people! Their love is transferred on every plate!  I see some ridiculous negative comments, but seriousky the food is amazing!
"The Best Trinidadian spot in Philly!!"
Can’t wait to try the doubles!!!
Good portions, fair pricing, nice ambience. This place should be busier!

We had a Friday evening reservation.  Seating was done quickly.  The person serving as our wait person was friendly and she did a nice job of appearing when needed.  Expectation vs reality is truly the way to sum up the food experience.  Online Menu versus Restaurant Menu: The menu online and the menu we were given were starkly different. Honestly it felt like bait and switch. There was no Phoulourie on the menu.   There were no Roti dishes or Buss Up Shut dishes (which equates to 10 missing items).  There were 3 sides missing from the menu (Callaloo, Rice and Beans, and the Boiled and Fried Cassava).  The menu had no drinks.  I don’t know if they actually had peanut punch or any of the others.  I asked if they had sorrel tea and the wait person advised they would check because they weren’t sure.  They did have it.  Sorrell Tea It was OK.  A bit sweeter than others I have had.  Corn Soup Quite tasty.  Looks nothing like the photo online, this was more of a puree.  Caribbean Salad I don’t know how long it was sitting around.  Mediocre at best.  Veggies Medley Served room temperature.  I am not sure why it wasn’t served hot.  The pumpkin puree was good.  There were 3 green beans on the plate.  The chickpea portion lack flavor.  I spent a lot of time pushing it around on the plate.  The rice was edible.  Chunky Vegetable Chow Mein Served cold.  Overly sweetened sauce.  Sweet Cinnamon Plantains Served cold. I have had these before elsewhere.  Cinnamon is usually an enhancement not the overkill that existed here.  Macaroni Pie It was good.  Unfortunately, it was also served cold.  I had high hopes based on other reviews.  Was the chef not there?  Something must have been wrong that night. It seemed like the food was pre-made and not kept up to temperature or something. It was quite a disappointing experience.  I would expect the food to be served at temperature and have some flavor. We ate what we could because we had an event to go to and no opportunity to get anything else for the night.  What I do know is that we won’t be going back again.  A few notes based on the owners response.  At no point did the server explain the reason for the limited menu.  And the place was not jammed packed.  You had a sign on your door indicating that you didn't have any openings between 6 and 7 p.m. however there were multiple empty tables there with reserved placards on them.  While you may work hard in your establishment, the statements of this experience are factual.
As a cook for over 16 years it's hard trying new places. Unfortunately can only go to a 3. Small unique place but slow service for a small place and Small portions on bland food :(
yummy
Food was good but they need to become better organized. But I will be going back for the fried wontons and blackened shrimps.
Food was great. The resturant was empty when we arrived so it was quiet. Our waiter was cool and knew the dishes well. I will say the goat was amazing. Will definitely order again.

This was my first time at this restaurant and I surprise my Trinidad girlfriend. She love the whole atmosphere since it reminds her of home. The quality of food was outstanding and seasonal very well. The young female host welcome us with open arms, she was very friendly. The price is very reason, so much that after our meal we ordered around round just to take home. We will definitely be going back.
Tasty wings with Famblo sauce, good salad with house dressing, yummy Tartufo dessert
The food was delicious😋😋😋..The staff were very professional and attentive. Had a great time at Flambo's👏👏👍👍
Amazing food, Great service and great experience. And really nice staff.

I was highly disappointed with Flambo.  I ordered 3 platter which were priced too high and I waited for about 35 minutes for takeout.  When I arrived home, I noticed part of my order was missing.  We called back and the owner was rude by saying "I'm really busy I'll call you back".  On top of all that the food wasn't that good.
very nice people working at this restaurant. The best roti ever and that carrot cake is awesome. love it
The BEST Carribean Food in Philadelphia. Great Staff & Amazing Service. Definitely Will Revisit Many Many Times.

My good friend is a native Trini and took me to this fine establishment for my first Trini experience. Absolutely everyone should try the roti. It is out of this world good. They serve it fresh and hot, and it's simply incredible. Make sure to ask for some pepper sauce to go on the side to mix with your dishes. It takes the food to the next level. The restaurant is family owned and run with really friendly folk. Highly recommended.
Had the Ox Tail on the waitresses recommendation.  Delicious and reasonable!
We love Flambo and we love Kev and Anthony... Best Trini spot in PA !!!!! Come one come all
Really great food and service!

Delicious food. We went on a Friday night and enjoyed the pannist. The restaurant is BYOB, but there is a $6 fee per bottle. After buying a small bottle of barefoot for a little over double the price, it seemed unreasonable to have to pay another 50% just to drink it. This should be improved in my opinion.  Response to Owner: I would recommend maybe waiving the fee on the first bottle. The concern that was expressed by staff was that larger parties tend to bring more bottles. So if that’s the case, maybe the establishment can begin charging after the first one or even two.

It truly does not get any better !  I was in Philadelphia this past weekend for a workshop. I and a couple of friends were looking for a restaurant that offered authentic cuisine from a culture with which we were not familiar. We had the great good fortune to happen upon Flambo.  We immediately were aware the ambiance was real, lovely and very relaxed. But we arrived to an overly full house due to a large private party being held there. When we shared our disappointment about being told there simply was no table available, the staff and chef/owner quickly conferred, regrouped and very graciously made space for us. They truly went out of their way to serve us. In my judgment the word service is used too often as simply a tag line. Flambo provides the real thing. Happily. Sincerely.  The food was in a word, yummy. Well prepared. Beautifully presented. And simply delicious.  We had not only a wonderful meal, but an exceptional experience. If I were a guest in the home of someone to whom I was dear, I would be thrilled to have been treated this well. In a restaurant, a rare gift.  The word that best describes this restaurant, its staff, and the heartfelt mission of Flambo, is love.  I live almost 4 hours away. I will surely return.  My thanks to the chef and owner Anthony, for having hosted us.

What a wonderful restaurant. The ambience is relaxed and welcoming, and casual yet charming. The food was outstanding, and the server and chef were very warm, friendly, and hard-working. Free parking (at a meter after hours) was available directly in front of the restaurant. I'm so glad to have stumbled upon this place while browsing online, because it immediately became a new favorite!
What an awesome pace, we came all the way from New York!  This place did not disappoint!
Awesome place!
Was very empty  but tasted alright.
Friendly staff but food is a poor representation of the islands, especially Trinidad and Tobago which they have a flag of outside the building.
Came to one of my fave spots, Flambo. I had an awesome server. The ambiance is romantic and hospitable. The food is tasty. Never any complaints. My goto spot when I need to do me.
Good food!
Loved it.  Great ambience. Great food.  Excellent service.
Awesome food awesome service awesome price....
Food was delicious and the service was so friendly and personal!
Good food nice service. Try it you will like it enjoy.😊😊😊😊
Had food from there the first time today the roti was great the stue chicken could have been seasoned a little better for my taste but it was good. Will be back to try some different dishes
Very good food and friendly service.
EXCELLENT food. Perfectly prepared, and the best roti I've ever had, including IN Trinidad.
The oxtail was amazing!
Did not enjoy the food here. The whole fish was rock hard. Spices were clearly not natural spices, but from an artificial powder. Just disappointed in this meal overall. Bad experience.
Very nice restaurant! Owners are nice, food is good! Satisfied!!
Good food, great price and plenty of parking on the street.
Delicious food in a beautiful atmosphere. Very reasonable prices and fast, friendly service. Tasty vegetarian options!
Delicious beautiful scene highly recommend
What a Spectacular Trinidadian Food Experience! If you want a fresh home cooked meal stop by, you will not be disappointed!
Great food great service great experience

Ate here today for a family dinner, food was delicious, and service was awesome !! Loved the Caribbean vibes as a fellow Trini🇹🇹 I really enjoyed my time here with the family. Thank you for a good dinner and a wonderful experience. We will definitely be coming back to eat again! 😋
Over priced,lacks the traditional condiments that goes with Trinidadian cuisine but food is good.Really that all I need to say to the response
Good food. Good service. Quiet and intimate atmosphere. BYOB. Can't complain. Will be adding to our list of chill spots.
Went last week with my family for my Trinidadian mother's birthday. The food was fantastic. Service was kind and prompt. I'd highly suggest it for your next Caribbean feast!
Finally found an authentic Trinidadian restaurant! Friendly staff, wholesome real owner. You'll love the ambiance, the food and the music. Support. Support. Support!

Well where do i begin?I walk in with my wife and am amazed about the feeling of the islands there.The female server was excellent and respectful.But the best part was the oxtail i got....the BEST in philly....without a doubt....don't believe me go try it yourselves.The chef actually came out and asked how everything was going!!! Most chefs couldn't care less about their customers unless they're rich or die hard so that's a pleasant surprise to me.My wife commented about their clean bathrooms.You know....i see all these bad reviews about this place and i wonder why?Five stars across the board for me.I will be coming back to experience the islands again.
Such a yummy place. The owner came out and greeted us. Can't wait to go back!
This was the worst ever ...wrong order price over priced for nothing your getting food was dry like should be ashamed to be called caribbean resturant

The only reason I'm giving this review a 4  is due to the portions being too small the price after taxes was approximately $18.50.  I went there today and got oxtails. The oxtails were very good but they only come with either white rice or rice & beans no vegetables or other side.  I chose the rice and peas which were also good. Most Carribbian spots offer at least 2 sides and I know at least 2 places that offer 3 for at $3-$4 less. The container was a small styrofoam container,  other than that food was good.

I’m trying to figure out how does this restaurant have 4.7 rating.... I am from Trinidad and Tobago. The food was very much tasteless. Missing so much flavor. The customer service was horrible. I asked for pholourie and the waiter said “let me ask the chef” then he came back and said “the chef said no it will take to long”...... huh????? I’m sorry what? That was definitely something to laugh at! Then I asked can we hold on to a menu (to look at and decide if we wanted to order to go)... his response was “no sorry but here’s a flyer that will show you our menu online”... I am always down to find a good Caribbean restaurant especially a Trinidadian restaurant but the service and food was horrible. Sorry to say but I will not be going back and will not recommend anyone to try this restaurant out....
Service, ambience and food was absolutely amazing. Beautiful for any and all occasions. #GirlsNight was absolutely amazing! Music was perfect and on point. Try the steamed wontons and pepper shrimp!

I ate here today with my son who just flew Into town.  The food and service was exceptional.  We had jerk wings, wontons, curry chicken, stew chicken and roti-the food came out hot, well seasoned. This review came from my son who is the worlds pickiest person and food critic. We will be back!!

Visiting from out of state I had a taste for Caribbean food and found this restaurant with a ton of 5 star ratings. We got there at 7:45 did not get our order taken until 8:15 (only 2 other tables there). We got our takeout at 9:20pm. Our Jerk wings were still bloody inside the rice and macaroni pie very tasteless.  Our server was very friendly and genuinely sorry for the wait and did explain there was only one cook. (The only reason for the second star)  In all I would not be returning and extremely upset we wasted a good $70 on that food.

Will not be returning to this place.....$70 wasted  Where do I begin we arrived at 7:45pm our order was taken @8:15pm (we were the 3rd table taken) when we finally got our take out at 9:20pm our 3 orders of jerk wings were still bloody inside, the rice was bland other stuff (oxtails,sweet plantains) were okay. My expectations were high because I love Caribbean food and with all the high ratings for this place I was looking forward to good food. I was visiting from New York and this wouldn’t be a reason to return.  I wish I knew how to add photos so I can show my bloody wings 😐
Took an hour to get our food. Some of our food was cold.
Really tasty food.  Really enjoyed the goat roti and the ox tail.  We will definitely be going again.
Love the service enviroment and most importantly the food.
Today was my first time there with my husband, and I must say the food was exceptional. Its now our favourite spot in town!
Absolutely delicious. Can't wait to go back. Loved my Roti with curried shrimp. Everyone had something different: oxtail, pelau, curried chicken, curried goat. All of it was awesome.
Had a wonderful dinner with my sisters...
Food, service and staff are all wonderful.
got some to go food from this place everything was delicious and the service was excellent. Definitely will go back soon!

Great food. Waitress was patient, amicable and attentive to our needs. We ordered the Pelau, which is a Trinandian favorite, and the Curry Goat entree. We also had a side of roti. It's BYOB. The ambiance is perfect for date night. They have classical caribbean music playing in the background. The decor is marvelous. The traditional paintings from carribean artists hang around the room and the carnival garments draw the clients to the culture. Attire: Polished casual If you're in the Philly area and you want to try something new or want a taste of the culture, definitely visit Flambo. At the end, the chef, Anthony, came to personally greet us. Very humble individual. We had a great date night.

We've ordered through GrubHub twice now, and things have been FANTASTIC! The macaroni pie thing satisfied my craving for mac and cheese, but it was grown up, I'm assuming Caribbean style? Excited to go into the restaurant, and real excited for these guys to come into the neighborhood! That roti bread stuff was awesome, too! No reason not to order from here or go here!
Food was very good,the owner comes to your table,they were very Personable and Accommodating nice Atmosphere food was very good I enjoyed everything about

Great food and great service! The food portions were amazing and quality was even better. The owner and chef came out to personally greet us and made us feel very welcomed there. I would highly recommend the place and def tell them you want to get family style dinner.
I am addicted to the oxtails. Very friendly owners.

Great Caribbean food!  My wife and I have ordered take out from here on multiple occasions and I have started taking coworkers here for a very unique lunch experience! The staff is both friendly and efficient.   I have tried several dishes and recommend that you stick with the more traditional Trinidadian offerings.
This place is excellent! Authentic Trinidadian food made from the heart. I will always eat here when in town! Curry Goat is the best
The plantains are delicious!!!! The staff is very nice and accommodating as well!! Very nice place!
This place is amazing, and the food is tasty. Alex and his father the owners are down to earth and the costumer service is great

The service was great and the food was delicious. The appearance of the restaurant was very elegant. The wait staff was pleasant and very interesting to talk to.The owner was equally pleasant. I will tell my friends&Family
Great service and great food. I would definitely recommend this place if you're in the area and looking to try something new.
The food was absolutely wonderful, from preparation to presentation Just beautiful & a peaceful and relaxing atmosphere. Thanks so much Anthony & Kevin!

This place is amazing. Very friendly service and authentic Trinidadian food! I highly recommend the oxtail, escovitch fish, and made to order buss up shot roti!! Also on the weekends the doubles is a must!!
The Food and Atmosphere was A 1....

Nice place. Food could have been better. I had the oxtails, rice & peas, and cabbage. the cabbage tasted like it was cooked in soy sacue way too salty for me . It was ok but it could have been better.

Fantastic Service and truly authentic Caribbean flavors.  Flambo is a promising step in the right direction in establishing a real culinary presence of authentic Trinidadian / Caribbean cusine in the Philadelphia culinary landscape.  Must try for those longing for some good freshly cooked Trini food.
Great atmosphere good Trinidadian dishes

I love eating here. Since I haven't made it to Trinidad and Tobago to meet my in laws and partake in the food my husband grew up eating, Flambo is the closest to it...according to Hubby! I love everything I've tried on the menu and if it's not on the menu...ask about it. The sorrell taste so fresh and the pepper sauce made everything perfect!! I loved this place!!!
Good people, good food, I highly recommend!
The Owner, Staff made me feel like home. O the food is delicious
Awesome service!  Kevin u r the best!

Just left and they have the best oxtail I've everrr had. The atmosphere is great you feel like you're ii the islands not broad and parish great service...you gotta check this place out of your wanting authentic island food.

Full disclosure: I live on the second floor above Flambo. The restaurant owner is my landlord. That said, I am addicted to the curried shrimp. I have had it at least four times. Be sure to ask about the roti. What a great way to enjoy the great sauce! I think I just decided to make it five this week.
(Translated by Google) Simply excellent. 😅  (Original) Simplemente excelente. 😅

This place is absolutely great! The food is filling and delicious! The staff are great people. My family and I got to sit and talk with the cook/owner of the restaurant and he is an amazing, welcoming  individual! The restaurant is very clean and well kept with great music. If anyone is looking for good Caribbean food I would go here!
Love Flambo it's culture, the staff, and the food is amazing. I cannot believe they only been opened for four months. Anthony is a warm spirited person. Will definitely be back!

I came for a Caribbean experience and was pleasantly surprise of the authentic food. Flambo food is underpriced! It was delicious, it was tasty, and the service was on point!! I highly recommend this restaurant!

There is something about this place that makes you want to come back for more. This is that place where you think of your mom's wholesome home cooked meal. The ambience and the staff makes you feel like you're on a mini vacation from the city. Love!
Their food is amazing, and always on point👌👌👌

I went in for take out and to serve my curiosity and I was very impressed. Very nice atmosphere and a lovely place might I add. I waited at the bar and had nice convocation with the owner about everything from the food to cell phones (I'm the guy that paid with his phone). Let's but not least the food was excellent, I will be returning for the done in experience.
First time having trini food and i loved it great job on the food and nice environment

This resturant has by far the best Caribbean food in Philadelphia. I came out for their brunch and had bake and shark, doubles and aloo pie. Their server Kevin is awesome. Very polite and attentive. Overall, I will definitely be back again and try their dinner menu.
Flambo is a great place to relax and enjoy great good from a great Chefe, it is so great that G.E  Marriage ministry is having there valentine dinner at Flambo. GO FLAMBO

I was just there on Friday, with my good friend and my 5 year old son. The Decor is beautiful, especially in comparison to what the place looked like before flambo. I was a bit concerned because there isn't a kids menu (not an issue), but our wonderful waiter Anthony was gracious enough to make a kid sized portion of stewed chicken and rice for my little boy. My son, who is a very picky eater, demolished the plate! My friend and I shared escovitch. We ordered some roti for the table which came with a portion of goat, potatoes and chickpeas. The entire meal was delicious! Anthony was a magnificent host/server/cook. We will be back again to try the other offerings on the menu.
I went 3 times, the Place is amazing and breathtaking the food is delicious.
The food here is great! The prices are great! The restaurant is very family friendly! Definitely recommend it anyone looking to get some awesome Caribbean food.

Went here with a group of friends and everyone enjoyed their food. Right on board and fast and easy seating. Doubles and pepper shrimp is a must and can't beat the price for authentic Caribbean food! The staff was great and suggested foods since it was our first time at the restaurant. It's also BYOB which is always a plus!
